The article discusses a joint statement by the Presidents of Kazakhstan, Russia, and the United States regarding their commitment to combat nuclear proliferation and terrorism. Since 2004, the three countries have been working together to eliminate the remnants of nuclear testing activities at the former Semipalatinsk Test Site and make it safe and secure. The Presidents have personally overseen the progress of these projects, and significant work has been completed. The enhanced security measures have made the site nearly secure, showcasing successful trilateral cooperation in nuclear security and non-proliferation.